name: OpenSSL 3.4.1
body:
OpenSSL 3.4.1 is a security patch release. The most severe CVE fixed in this release is High.

This release incorporates the following bug fixes and mitigations:

* Fixed RFC7250 handshakes with unauthenticated servers don't abort as expected. ([CVE-2024-12797](https://www.openssl.org/news/vulnerabilities.html#CVE-2024-12797))

* Fixed timing side-channel in ECDSA signature computation. ([CVE-2024-13176](https://www.openssl.org/news/vulnerabilities.html#CVE-2024-13176))
